				<h1>The IRC core rewrite, almost done.</h1>
				<div class="date">2010-06-07 23:58 UTC</div>
				<hr/>

<p>
Over the last month I've rewritten most of the IRC core of BitlBee.
This was on the roadmap for a long time, but more a long term plan.
Many feature requests (the most important ones being separate control
channels per account or per contact group) were postponed "until the IRC core rewrite is
done", etc. Now, this work is finally done (or at least nearing completion).
</p>

<p>
The branch can be found at
<a href="http://code.bitlbee.org/wilmer/ui-fix/">http://code.bitlbee.org/wilmer/ui-fix/</a>.
<a href="http://code.bitlbee.org/debian/wilmer-ui-fix/">Debian packages</a>
are also available, as usual. The branch is based on the killerbee branch,
so it also has the file transfer/libpurple functionality.
</p>

<p>
Read more on the <a href="http://wiki.bitlbee.org/UiFix">BitlBee Wiki</a>.
</p>

<p>
<i>Update (2010-06-08 21:31 (UTC)): testing.bitlbee.org is now running
this code on port 6669. Feel free to give it a try!</i>
</p>
</div>

